# Relay Agent System

File-based multi-agent system. Agents are persistent identities surviving context death. Everything is a markdown file. Filesystem is the message bus.

See `workspace/CLAUDE.md` for the full reference, including agent structure, subagent registry, command catalog, principal/project model, and skill promotion.

## Core Rules (always-on)

1. Files are the protocol. No state outside the filesystem.
2. RELAY.md is a full rewrite, never append.
3. Learnings INDEX is computed, never hand-edited.
4. Messages never deleted. Archive only.
5. Tasks track kanban. Done tasks always have an Outcome.
6. Agents are identities; subagents are services.
7. AGENT.md stays lean. Deep knowledge lives in Learnings.
8. Retire order: Learnings → RELAY → Tasks → Messages → Session → commit workspace.
9. Delegate file mechanics to subagents.
10. Skip `.gitkeep`. Only `.md` files are content.
11. Never mock tests. Hit real staging. A mocked test is a lie.
12. Workspace committed on every retire.
13. Never modify repos you don't own. READ anywhere, WRITE only your declared repo + `workspace/agents/{callsign}/`. Other repos need changes → `messenger` the owning agent. Most-violated rule. No exceptions.
14. Read PRINCIPAL.md + PROJECT.md at every employ. Update PRINCIPAL.md on standing corrections.

## File naming

`{slug}--{from}--{YYYYMMDD-HHmm}.md` — kebab-case slug, no spaces. Double dashes separate fields. ISO 8601 timestamps in content.

## Message format

```markdown
FROM: {sender callsign}
DATE: {YYYY-MM-DD}
PRIORITY: {normal | high | urgent}

{Body. Specific, actionable. Reader has zero context from your session.}
```

## Task format

```markdown
# {Title}

- **From:** {creator callsign}
- **Assigned to:** {assignee callsign}
- **Created:** {ISO 8601}
- **Priority:** {low | normal | high | urgent}

## Description
{what needs doing}

## Acceptance Criteria
{how we know it's done}

## Notes
{updated during execution}

## Outcome
{filled when Done}
```

## Learning format

```markdown
# {Title}

- **Date:** {ISO 8601}
- **Tags:** {comma-separated}

## Context
{what was happening}

## Learning
{the insight}

## Application
{when to apply}
```
